Race payload:
{
  "name": "Aarakocra",
  "description": "The Aarakocra are bird-like skyborn people who dwell among sheer cliffs, storm-carved peaks, and hidden mountain sanctuaries far above ordinary kingdoms. Their culture values freedom, vigilance, and aerial mastery, with warriors trained to read wind currents the way others read roads. In battle, they use height, speed, and precision instead of brute force, diving from above with wing-mounted blades before rising beyond reach again. Their command of air is not always true spellcasting, but an instinctive harmony with wind pressure, momentum, and open sky, making them exceptional scouts, messengers, skirmishers, and support allies in wide battlefield terrain.",
  "species": "BEASTFOLK",
  "characterTypes": "SUPPORT_CHARACTER",
  "affinities": {
    "WEAPON": [
      "Wing Blades"
    ],
    "ELEMENTAL": [
      "AIR"
    ],
    "SKILL": [
      "Aerial Mobility"
    ]
  },
  "attributes": [
    {
      "Strength": 52
    },
    {
      "Agility": 91
    },
    {
      "Physical Defense": 43
    },
    {
      "Magical Defense": 61
    },
    {
      "Mana": 29
    },
    {
      "Intelligence": 72
    },
    {
      "Courage": 76
    },
    {
      "Patience": 68
    },
    {
      "Ego": 42
    },
    {
      "Pride": 64
    }
  ],
  "weaknesses": [
    "Grounding, Wing injuries, binding effects, nets, gravity magic, or cramped terrain severely reduce the Aarakocra’s combat effectiveness.",
    "Low Physical Durability, Their lighter skeletal structure improves flight but makes them vulnerable to heavy melee strikes and crushing attacks.",
    "Enclosed Spaces, Caves, tunnels, dense forests, and indoor battlefields limit flight paths and weaken their strongest tactical advantage."
  ],
  "skills": [
    "Sky Strike (REGULAR)",
    "Gale Force (HEAVY)",
    "Soaring Escape (UNIQUE)",
    "Aerial Agility (PASSIVE)"
  ]
}

Art style: cinematic AAA fantasy RPG realism, dramatic lighting, realistic anatomy, detailed armor, volumetric shadows, high-end game trailer look

Requirements:
- Show the race clearly as a full-body character
- Use details from race attributes, affinities, resistances, weaknesses, skills, and type
- No text, no watermark, no UI
- Clean character silhouette
- Highly detailed costume, anatomy, weapon, aura, and environment
- create 3 distinct variants of the character based on the same race data, varying pose, facial expression, gender (if applicable), lighting but keeping the character design consistent across variants.
- create a 4th variant that has multiple of the same character in a dynamic action pose, showcasing the character's design and skills in motion.

